title: For Sale:  Mint condition Irish Contract Lee Enfield No4. Mk2
postcontent: I'm selling my Enfield No4 Mk2. The serial number is in the PF328XXX range which makes this one of the fabled Irish contract rifles.  For those not familiar, after WWII when these rifles were at their best fit and finish, Ireland contracted England to build them rifles, for whatever reason the rifles were never delivered and sat in a warehouse for decades until being sold off as surplus in the 90's. That makes this rifle unissued and until I received it, unfired.  These are regarded as the best shooting Enfield rifles available.  I purchased it from a collector that was the original purchaser, he never shot it and I've only put 20 shots through it. There are some minor safe bumps but other than that, the rifle is simply immaculate, it's like a snapshot in time.  The rifle has a 1954 production date.  I'm including a matching bayonet and a box of ammunition.  I see these getting bid up to the $700 range on Gunbroker on the rare times they come up for sale, I'm just asking $500 to make the sale easier, buyer pays transfer fees and I'm located in Newark. This does qualify as a C&R for those of you with your license.  Cash is preferable but I'm open to trades as well, let me know what you have.  I'm not looking for milsurps at this time.

5. Is flash suppressed.

Buffalo Bore is introducing these three different heavy, yet standard pressure loadings for 38 SPL. These offerings are loaded at standard pressure, but they are much more powerful than normal 38SPL ammo. These loads will not harm older more fragile revolvers. So, these loads are safe for use in ANY 38 SPL revolver, provided it is in normal working condition. As stated above, the "POWER" level of these loads is really closer to a typical +P power level, but the pressure is standard. All three of these loads are flash suppressed, so firing them in the dark wont blind you.
